# Cursor Rules — Claimb iOS

## Vision / Scope
- iPhone-only app. Swift 6, iOS 17+.
- Local-first: SwiftData for persistence; no backend.
- Feature focus: Post-game coaching (3 bullets + 1 drill), Champion Pool guidance, lightweight Home insights.

## Architecture North Star
- Single responsibility. Prefer 100–300 LOC per service file.
- Shared logic in Swift Package `Packages/ClaimbCore`.
- App target contains only UI, DI, StoreKit, BackgroundTasks, Notifications.
- Avoid conditional compilation; if needed, isolate in tiny adapters.

## Coding Style (make Cursor follow this)
- Use async/await + URLSession. Avoid completion-handler APIs unless bridging.
- No singletons. Use lightweight DI via `Environment` (struct of clients/services).
- Protocol-first for external deps (RiotClient, CoachingService, Keychain, Logger, Haptics).
- Keep functions ≤ 40 LOC; extract pure helpers for KPI/math/formatting.
- Naming: `<Feature>View`, `<Feature>Coordinator`, `<Thing>Service`, `<Thing>Client`, `<Thing>Adapter`.

## Data & Persistence
- SwiftData only. One container factory in ClaimbCore.
- Models: small, explicit. Version them early (add reserved fields only if necessary).
- Cache everything by `matchId`. Add stable unique constraints where sensible.
- Coaching cache is keyed by `matchId`; never re-call OpenAI if cached.

## Networking (Riot/OpenAI)
- All HTTP in ClaimbCore. No networking in Views.
- Add simple rate limiter (e.g., 1 req / 1.2s burst-friendly).
- Implement ETag/If-None-Match for Riot GETs via URLCache.
- Errors: define small error enums; never bubble raw URLError to UI.

## Paywall & Quotas (StoreKit 2)
- One subscription group: Monthly + Annual; Monthly has 7-day trial.
- `Entitlements.isSubscriber` + `Quota.consumeIfAvailable()` gate `CoachingService`.
- Free tier: X analyses per week, configurable via a constant.
- UI reacts immediately to entitlement changes.

## Performance & UX
- Sessions are 60–120 sec. Design for one-hand use.
- Glanceable cards > tables. One primary action per screen.
- Show loading/error/empty states explicitly; no silent failures.
- Haptics for success/error. Avoid heavy charts in v1.

## Accessibility & Localization
- Dynamic Type compatible. Use SF Symbols with labels.
- Minimum: English only, but wrap strings for easy localization later.

## Security & Secrets
- No API keys hard-coded in source. Use build settings or config files excluded from VCS.
- Use Keychain adapter for tokens; never persist secrets in SwiftData.

## File Size Budgets
- Services: 100–300 LOC (split if larger).
- Views: ≤ 200 LOC (extract subviews).
- Do not add a dependency unless it saves >150 LOC AND reduces complexity.

## Don’ts
- No desktop assumptions (file watchers, overlays, multiwindow).
- No premature generics or over-abstracted factories.
- No background polling > 1/day without explicit reason.

## Testability
- Provide `…Mock` for each protocol in `Tests`.
- Move parsing and KPI logic into pure functions with unit tests.
- Keep DI pluggable so tests can inject stubs.

## Pull Requests & Commits (help Cursor structure work)
- PR title: `[feature] short summary` or `[fix] short summary`.
- Each PR includes: scope, before/after notes, screenshots if UI.
- Commit messages are imperative: `Add RiotHTTPClient with ETag cache`.

## Ready-to-use Prompts (inline helpers for Cursor)
- “Create a `RiotHTTPClient` conforming to `RiotClient` using async/await, URLSession, simple 1.2s rate limiter, and ETag/If-None-Match via URLCache. Keep file <200 LOC. Map JSON to `MatchSummary` safely.”
- “Refactor this view >200 LOC into subviews. Preserve logic, extract `KPIBadge`, `MatchCard`, keep parent ≤ 180 LOC.”
- “Add StoreKit 2 entitlements helper returning `isSubscriber`. Include purchase/restore flows, sandbox notes. Keep logic isolated from views.”
- “Implement `PaywallGuard` decorator for `CoachingService` with `isSubscriber` + `hasFreeQuota`. Throw `subscriptionRequired` when neither holds.”

## Acceptance Checks (Cursor can aim for these)
- App starts < 1.5s cold; Home shows “Next best 3 champs” and last-match card.
- Press “Analyze last match” → returns cached coaching instantly or fetches once, then caches.
- Toggle entitlement in Sandbox → paywall state updates immediately.
- Airplane mode → last-known matches and coaching still visible.


